<subSubSection id="9EB0CD8AEC07DF4AE2C6C590B5098432" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" type="type material">
<paragraph id="0C6E57F7EF7A5E1D22AAB14BCD26FFF2" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E00C997CD740AFDBF32B380B3D30B927" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
Holotype male, 
<emphasis id="5383D77857C8560D25C353F01584B733" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">CHINA</emphasis>
: Hainan: Baoting, 80 m, 21.vii.1960, S. F. Li leg. (IZCAS).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D18FE9D129AA76ADFF79DA5390508AA9" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
Paratypes. 
<emphasis id="0C49B6D8D2DBA1B7EF13A93AA5F39D5F" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">CHINA</emphasis>
: Hainan: 6 males, 24 females, Baoting, 80 m, 23., 24. and 27.vii.1960, S. F. Li, X. Z. Zhang &amp; C. Q. Li leg.; 11 males, 15 females, Tongshi, 340 m, 23., 24. and 25.vi., 31.vii., 1., 4. and 6.viii.1960, S. F. Li, X. Z. Zhang &amp; C. Q. Li leg.; 1 male, 1 female, Yinggen, 200 m, 4.v. and 5.vii.1960, S. F. Li leg.; 1 female, Shuiman, 640 m, 25.v.1960, C. Q. Li leg.; 2 males, Wanning, 10 m, 12., 13.iv.1960, S. F. Li &amp; C. Q. Li leg.; 3 females, Qiongzhong, 15-17.vii.1960, X. Z. Zhang &amp; C. Q. Li leg.; 2 males, 3 females, Kwangtung, 3., 4. and 5.iv., 13. and 26.viii.1934, C. Ho leg. (all IZCAS); 1 male, Mangrin, 9.vi.1904; 1 female, Mon Boi, 29.v.1904 (both BMNH).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B651485410DD98833D5A2F0F89ACDB2A" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F38AD0AAEF312DF3E971CA3B4C12E203" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="82860E84FB905FDF53A5C9906AD94579" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">
<taxonomicName id="C34D212CDE33F66943BEC6C11B85100A" authorityName="Song, Chen &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus hainanensis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="D4323C6AF79FBB50912A49ABA7DC36CC" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">Orthopagus hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. n. is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="102890A302153B3F7F18E0AB07E4E5B5" genus="O." lsidName="O. lunulifer" pageId="4" pageNumber="373" rank="species" species="lunulifer">
<emphasis id="D6CE2D66E19DF8DC8A167D14EFFC48DF" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="373">O. lunulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in most characters, but can be differentiated from 
<pageBreakToken id="9FBFA08A8A5F6E3D043B582F113CEA42" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
latter by the ivory white to pale ochraceous vertex with a pair of dark brown spots on each side of midline in basal third (in 
<taxonomicName id="CA74D21E9978B72664DFA6D5F6C676A5" genus="O." lsidName="O. lunulifer" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" rank="species" species="lunulifer">
<emphasis id="B3DAFED36D2E6AE62F06BF401BF245CB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">O. lunulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the vertex is nearly dark brown from base to apex) and the male segment X being elongate in dorsal view, with ratio of length to width near middle 1.9-2.0 (in 
<taxonomicName id="43AB1DC67D27F8FF585F3E78F635DE13" genus="O." lsidName="O. lunulifer" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" rank="species" species="lunulifer">
<emphasis id="B71B496030468D8C4B14D6857142AF54" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">O. lunulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male segment X is shorter and wider in dorsal view, with ratio of length to width near middle 1.2-1.3). 
<taxonomicName id="E9FCBA48BC0A767575500AB95F517710" authorityName="Song, Chen &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus hainanensis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="D9520A7FB78036C364D239BDDB2AD577" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Orthopagus hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. n. is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="87958CB5DD315FC48E81593C35421673" genus="O." lsidName="O. exoletus" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" rank="species" species="exoletus">
<emphasis id="B68B2D01CE9EA19CFAE22612AD2B233B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">O. exoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the predominantly light vertex but it differs from the latter by a slightly longer head, the male pygofer with dorso-posterior margin produced into a broad and short lobe in lateral view (the pygofer bears a larger tooth-like process dorso-posteriorly in 
<taxonomicName id="C61FB70C5249C8502D94AEAB2B7BC6A2" genus="O." lsidName="O. exoletus" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" rank="species" species="exoletus">
<emphasis id="CE654D5EEE45E1C1BD0D2A405A52A43D" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">O. exoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the aedeagus with two pairs of larger (more strongly inflated) dorsolateral membranous lobes and endosomal processes covered with minute spines (indistinct in 
<taxonomicName id="E2F23D88541955FA1850369B885FD287" genus="O." lsidName="O. exoletus" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" rank="species" species="exoletus">
<emphasis id="EC0967BD5239A99041506B3E6D96D267" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">O. exoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6F1752FF58A62532A9F785E65B41C8B1" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" type="description">
<paragraph id="643E18E82806A585E6F1707900DED58E" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1A7F2C051585787B5CEC8EC33AA36ED" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Measurements (5 males, 10 females). Body length (from apex of head to tip of forewings): male 11.7-12.9 mm, female 13.1-14.6 mm; head length (from apex of cephalic process to base of eyes): male 1.4-1.5 mm, female 1.5-1.6 mm; head width (including eyes): male 1.6-1.7 mm, female 1.6-1.7 mm; forewing length: male 9.3-10.3 mm, female 10.6-11.8 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D102E2C4A85771197BA73C1ED07A5B3" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">
Coloration. General coloration as in generic description (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F59D88C8AA5F6ABBBCA48DA5AB4C5AD7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus of Orthopagus species. (A, B) O. bartletti sp. n., male, holotype, Karnataka, India; (C, D) O. exoletus (Melichar), male and female, Sri Lanka; (E, F) O. hainanensis sp. n., male and female, paratypes, Hainan, China; (G, H) O. lunulifer Uhler, male and female, China; (I, J) O. philippinus Melichar, male and female, Philippines; (K, L) O. splendens (Germar), male and female, China." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221398" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">2E-F</figureCitation>
). Head ivory white to pale ochraceous, vertex with basal corners castaneous, a pair of large fuscous patches on each side of midline at basal third, and pale fuscous apical diamond-shaped spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4F4935B94E94E3E52B7A99750D1C50A0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6A</figureCitation>
); frons pale with series of small pale fuscous spots along intermediate and lateral carinae, base without distinct dark spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="93E5B64EA0B3A71362A67CB02067E75B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6C</figureCitation>
). Forewing pattern as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1918B51E33FEE022B557A86438FC30AE" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Forewing of Orthopagus species. (A) O. bartletti sp. n.; (B) O. exoletus (Melichar); (C) O. hainanensis sp. n.; (D) O. lunulifer Uhler; (E) O. philippinus Melichar; (F) O. splendens (Germar)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221399" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">3C</figureCitation>
. Hind wing membrane with a relatively narrow dark brown streak along the apical portion of CuA1 vein, extending along hind wing apical margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E703BA8CAC1EFF3BEA69A81EFCC29210" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">
Structure. Cephalic process (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5F95E0A31AE91C9EAA0A536B360E4417" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6A-C</figureCitation>
) relatively elongate. Vertex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D2ADA39EC9C3CA97175509E8E6A271A1" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6A</figureCitation>
) with ratio of length at midline to width between eyes 1.65-1.75. Transition of vertex to frons narrowly rounded in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F828BA8B15A0E3E8B93B50408495F05" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6B</figureCitation>
). Frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6001B395B8C9F0E1C8D9C5D862260ED0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6C</figureCitation>
) relatively narrow, with ratio of length at midline to maximum width 2.7-2.9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF1C1FAD334DBD20222B08CADC224EC0" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">
Male genitalia. Pygofer in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="072A6EBCFA2C84280763F3DFC40CF504" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6E</figureCitation>
) with dorso-posterior margin produced into a broad and relatively short blunt lobe; in ventral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29E4AF11EE77F89D1B7E07E78A625AE8" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6F</figureCitation>
) much longer than in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FF940812A4B306107C17F7E996D1CF79" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6D</figureCitation>
) with ratio of ventral to dorsal length about 4.2. Gonostyles (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BF7B788B7AAFCD1D29268D83F6DBD1CC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6E-F</figureCitation>
) large, broad medially, with dorsal margin weakly sinuate. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3FA120F95E02D57D8C51AC1ED33E5FF5" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6G-I</figureCitation>
) with endosomal processes covered with minute spines, extended posteriad and strongly curved dorso-anteriad; phallobase with one pair of large, strongly inflated dorsolateral lobes, their apices gradually convergent and tapering posteriad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5E72705017F558C2F76D6822CB038CCC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6G-I</figureCitation>
), and one pair of small, thumb-like ventral lobes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="14E7111A09DD817A91E8E29B8D54DC1C" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6I</figureCitation>
). Segment X relatively narrow and elongate, in lateral view, narrow basally, widening beyond middle, apex subacute (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="142AA3EBE3235BE395517CF14D7699D4" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6E</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, widest medially, with ratio of length to width 1.9-2.0 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7DE52B770084FE89E930039DF69B7E51" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view. (B) Head and pronotum, lateral view. (C) Head and pronotum, ventral view. (D) Male segment X and pygofer, dorsal view. (E) Male pygofer, gonostyles, and segment X, lateral view. (F) Male pygofer and gonostyles, ventral view. (G) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (H) Aedeagus, lateral view. (I) Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221402" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AB08DD6D23E225E26CFA20E575476E8" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">
Female genitalia as in generic description (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE4DB5BCDD3AFB39CDC9CD1DD6DB5730" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Orthopagus hainanensis sp. n. (A) Female terminalia and ectodermal genital ducts, dorsal view. (B) Female terminalia and ectodermal genital ducts, lateral view. (C) Female terminalia and ectodermal genital ducts, ventral view. (D) Gonapophysis VIII, dorsolateral view. (E) Gonapophysis IX, ventral view. (F) Gonapophysis IX, lateral view. (G) Gonoplacs, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.94.26859.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/221404" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">7A-G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0DA6ADB7A96BA2BBFA69D4C1A88D8CC9" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="66C486B535E8D1153F2C78E9DC33AC98" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F26FA5C5988F0275AFEB0AA1C08D5AA" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">
The new species is named for its occurrence in Hainan Island, China. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="55AD0266796E5C3EB6DB4CDF7CB6DCF7" authorityName="Song, Chen &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus hainanensis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="09308107CCEFCEEB65FDCE266393734B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Orthopagus hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to be treated as a latinized adjective in nominative singular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3048514E7979ECC31A295A41C03CDE0" pageId="5" pageNumber="374" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AC67E942FBC7D0AF121AEC5E8E2840F7" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE3BCE655067DB9FC438FB0966F8346F" pageId="5" pageNumber="374">So far only known from Hainan Island, China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
